        &lt;h1 class="c-page-hero__title [ u-fs36 u-fs50@l u-lh1 u-wbbw ]" dir="ltr" lang="en"&gt;
      U.S. Snaps up Venezuela’s Oil and Rare Minerals in Race for Supplies
    &lt;/h1&gt;&lt;!-- /.c-page-hero__title --&gt;

    
          &lt;div class="c-page-hero__teaser [ u-ptserif u-fs18 u-fs15@m u-fs18@l u-fsi ]" dir="ltr" lang="en"&gt;
        &lt;div class="word-wrap"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Even before the price of oil spiked, the Trump administration was eyeing Venezuela’s natural resources. There is now more urgency to getting access to petroleum and critical minerals. In this Q&amp;amp;A, Crisis Group experts Bram Ebus and Alexandra Fuenmayor Starr explain the challenges lying ahead.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- /.c-page-hero__teaser --&gt;
